  hotspots:
  - title: Further Down the Walkway Near the Torii
    body: "This part of the garden is a good place to slow down and pay attention
      to composition: the framing of the path, the placement of stone and plants,
      and the way each turn changes what you see. That feeling of discovery is intentional
      and comes directly from Rohoen\u2019s miegakure design, where the landscape
      is meant to unfold gradually rather than all at once. In that way, the garden
      teaches something subtle but important: beauty is not only in the destination,
      but in the act of moving carefully through the space."
    yaw: 0
    pitch: 0
    icon: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 7d2865e2b884e1a46be7144719039f15, type: 2}
